      "span_text": "Following fixation in 4% paraformaldehyde (see ), tissues were transferred to microcentrifuge tubes, washed 5 times (30 min each) in 80 mM phosphate buffer containing 2% Triton X-100 and 0.1% sodium azide (PTA), and incubated in streptavidin conjugated to Alexa Fluor 546 (Molecular Probes, #S-11225) diluted 1:1,000 to 1:2,000 in PTA (24-48 h, room temperature)."
